0008|- [HelpText]
0009|*The control words appearing in the extra specifications of
0010|*the GPLOT (PLOT) operations can be defined by the user.
0011|*All such definitions are saved in a text file (Survo device
0012|*driver) and maintained easily by the SAVEP and LOADP operations
0013|*of Survo.
0015|*The default device driver for the GPLOT operation is given as
0016|*crt_dev=<name_of_file> in the auxiliary file SURVO.APU in the
S   |         <            >
0017|*Survo directory.
0019|*Most of the specifications in GPLOT schemes can be given like
0020|*GRID=([RED][line_width(2)]),XY
0021|*where the driver dependent part has always the form
0022|*  ([...][...]...[...]),
0023|*The words in brackets (like [RED] and [line_width(2)]) have to be
0024|*defined in the driver.
0026|*To override the default driver, use INCLUDE=<name_of_driver>
S   |                                             <              >
0027|*in your GPLOT scheme.
0029|*New drivers can be built by using default drivers as models.
0031|- shadow a: [LINK(q11_01.html)]
