0062|- [HelpText]
0063|#GPLOT /PALETTE <old_PAL_file>,<new_PAL_file>
S   |                <            > <            >
0064|*displays the colors represented by the <old_PAL_file> (with default
S   |                                        <            >
0065|*extension .PAL) with their RGB values ranging from 0 to 1000.
0066|SThe default path for .PAL files is the current data path and
S   |                                        88888888888888888
0067|*secondarily <Survo>\U\SYS .
S   |             <     >
0069|*The RGB values are rescaled to range from 0 to 63 during editing.
0070|*The user can edit the RGB values by moving the cursor and increasing
0071|*and decreasing the values by + and - keys. The colors will be changing
0072|*accordingly.
0073|*Finally, by pressing ENTER the edited RGB values will be saved as a
0074|*<new_PAL_file>. The original scaling from 0 to 1000 will be resumed.
S   | <            >
