0083|- [HelpText]
0084|*Any character font in the current Windows environment can be used in
0085|*SURVO MM screen plots.
0086|*Names of available fonts and text samples using them is obtained
0087|*by activating the sucro command
0088|*/FONTS .
0089|*Any text item in the graph can be given with a [FONT(font_name,size)]
0090|*code attribute. For example, using the "Times New Roman" font of size 20 in the
0091|*plot header and in `red' color and in italics can be indicated by
0093|*HEADER=[FONT(Times_New_Roman,20)][RED][ITALIC],Steiner_circles
0095|*Please note that spaces must be replaced by '_'s in these notations.
0096|*All code attributes for screen plotting are defined in the CRT16.DEV text file
0097|*(in directory <Survo>\U\SYS).
S   |               <     >
0099|*For compability with earlier Survos and PostScript plotting CRT16.DEV includes
0100|*shorthand ready-made definitions like (this equals to the above HEADER):
0102|*HEADER=[TimesI(20)][RED],Steiner_circles
0104|*Similarly [TimesB(12)] is the same as [FONT(Times_New_Roman,12)][BOLD].
0106|*GPLOT /FRAME  / Load the setup by '+' and activate this line!
